spec: mp3436
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(multiprocessing)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html"
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.managers.html"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source code"
    - "any proprietary source"
  notes:
    - "Wave 676 (mp3436): __le__, __gt__, __ge__ dict-presence (x<=y, x>y, x>=y) for multiprocessing types."
    - "Theme: __le__/__gt__/__ge__ dict-presence (x<=y, x>y, x>=y)."
    - "All values False — these types do not define ordering comparison operators in their own __dict__."
    - "All values verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13."
    - "Classes covered: multiprocessing.Process, pool.Pool, pool.AsyncResult, pool.MapResult, managers.SyncManager, managers.BaseListProxy, managers._BaseDictProxy, managers._BaseSetProxy."
    - "Key finding (__le__): all 8 multiprocessing classes return false for __le__. <= delegates to __le__ when defined in the class's own __dict__. multiprocessing.Process: a subprocess lifecycle manager with no __le__ in its own __dict__. pool.Pool/AsyncResult/MapResult: work-dispatch and result-handle types with no custom __le__ in their own __dict__. managers.SyncManager: server process manager with no __le__ in its __dict__. managers.BaseListProxy: proxies list — BaseListProxy does not define __le__ in its own __dict__ despite defining other collection protocol methods. managers._BaseDictProxy: proxies dict; __le__ is absent from its own __dict__. managers._BaseSetProxy: proxies set; __le__ is not defined in its own __dict__."
    - "Key finding (__gt__): all 8 multiprocessing classes return false for __gt__. > delegates to __gt__ when defined in the class's own __dict__. multiprocessing types do not define __gt__ in their own __dict__; greater-than comparison falls back to inherited behavior (raises TypeError at runtime since object has no __gt__). The proxy types (_BaseSetProxy, _BaseDictProxy, BaseListProxy) relay operations to the managed server process via IPC but do not define __gt__ in their own __dict__. multiprocessing.Process: identity-based semantics by inheritance; __gt__ is absent from Process.__dict__. pool.Pool/AsyncResult/MapResult/SyncManager: no __gt__ defined in their own __dict__."
    - "Key finding (__ge__): all 8 multiprocessing classes return false for __ge__. >= delegates to __ge__ when defined in the class's own __dict__. multiprocessing types define no ordering protocol in their own __dict__. managers.BaseListProxy key note: BaseListProxy defines __getitem__, __setitem__, __delitem__, __len__, __contains__, __add__, __mul__, and other collection protocol methods in its __dict__, but __ge__ is not among them. managers._BaseDictProxy: defines dict proxy methods in its __dict__, but not __ge__. managers._BaseSetProxy: defines set proxy methods in its __dict__, but not __ge__. multiprocessing.Process/pool.Pool/AsyncResult/MapResult/SyncManager: process-management types with no __ge__ in their own __dict__."
    - "All 24 values in this wave are false. multiprocessing is a process-based concurrency library; its types interact exclusively through explicit method calls, subprocess lifecycle management, and IPC — not through ordering protocol overrides in any class __dict__."
    - "Cross-wave summary for mp subjects:"
    - "  Wave 658 (mp3166): __add__/__sub__/__mul__ — BaseListProxy __add__=true, __mul__=true; others false."
    - "  Wave 659 (mp3181): __truediv__/__floordiv__/__mod__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 660 (mp3196): __pow__/__lshift__/__rshift__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 661 (mp3211): __and__/__or__/__xor__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 662 (mp3226): __radd__/__rsub__/__rmul__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 663 (mp3241): __rtruediv__/__rfloordiv__/__rmod__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 664 (mp3256): __rpow__/__rlshift__/__rrshift__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 665 (mp3271): __rand__/__ror__/__rxor__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 666 (mp3286): __iadd__/__isub__/__imul__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 667 (mp3301): __itruediv__/__ifloordiv__/__imod__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 668 (mp3316): __ipow__/__ilshift__/__irshift__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 669 (mp3331): __iand__/__ior__/__ixor__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 670 (mp3346): __neg__/__pos__/__abs__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 671 (mp3361): __invert__/__floor__/__ceil__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 672 (mp3376): __trunc__/__round__/__index__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 673 (mp3391): __int__/__float__/__complex__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 674 (mp3406): __bool__/__str__/__repr__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 675 (mp3421): __hash__/__eq__/__lt__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 676 (mp3436): __le__/__gt__/__ge__ — all false for all 8."
  created_at: "2026-04-13"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __le__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__le__')
#
# All 8 multiprocessing classes return false for __le__.
# <= delegates to __le__ when defined in the class's own __dict__.
# multiprocessing.Process: a subprocess lifecycle manager; <= is not
#   part of the Process API. __le__ is absent from Process.__dict__.
# pool.Pool/AsyncResult/MapResult: work-dispatch and result-handle types
#   with no custom __le__ defined in their own __dict__.
# managers.SyncManager: server process manager with no __le__ in its
#   __dict__.
# managers.BaseListProxy: proxies list — BaseListProxy defines some
#   collection protocol methods (__add__, __mul__, etc.) but does not
#   define __le__ in its own __dict__.
# managers._BaseDictProxy: proxies dict operations; __le__ is not defined
#   in its own __dict__.
# managers._BaseSetProxy: proxies set operations; __le__ is not defined
#   in its own __dict__.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table mp3436.le:
  description: "multiprocessing types __le__ dict-presence checks; wave 676"
  kind: python_call_eq
  version: ">=3.9"
  error_model: python_exceptions
  category: dict_contains
  id_prefix: mp3436

  columns: [id, function, args, expected]
  rows:
    - ["mp3436001", operator.contains, [multiprocessing.Process.__dict__,                 "__le__"], false]
    - ["mp3436002", operator.contains, [multiprocessing.pool.Pool.__dict__,               "__le__"], false]
    - ["mp3436003", operator.contains, [multiprocessing.pool.AsyncResult.__dict__,        "__le__"], false]
    - ["mp3436004", operator.contains, [multiprocessing.pool.MapResult.__dict__,          "__le__"], false]
    - ["mp3436005", operator.contains, [multiprocessing.managers.SyncManager.__dict__,    "__le__"], false]
    - ["mp3436006", operator.contains, [multiprocessing.managers.BaseListProxy.__dict__,  "__le__"], false]
    - ["mp3436007", operator.contains, [multiprocessing.managers._BaseDictProxy.__dict__, "__le__"], false]
    - ["mp3436008", operator.contains, [multiprocessing.managers._BaseSetProxy.__dict__,  "__le__"], false]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __gt__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__gt__')
#
# All 8 multiprocessing classes return false for __gt__.
# > delegates to __gt__ when defined in the class's own __dict__.
# multiprocessing types do not define __gt__ in their own __dict__; equality
#   falls back to inherited behavior from object (raises TypeError).
# managers.BaseListProxy: relays collection operations to the managed server
#   process via proxy methods, but does not define __gt__ in its __dict__.
# managers._BaseDictProxy: proxies dict operations; __gt__ is not defined
#   in its own __dict__.
# managers._BaseSetProxy: proxies set operations; __gt__ is not defined
#   in its own __dict__.
# multiprocessing.Process: __gt__ is absent from Process.__dict__.
# pool.Pool/AsyncResult/MapResult/SyncManager: process-management types with
#   no __gt__ customization in their own __dict__.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

